replies.body:
"Null" represents a variable with no value. It means that the data that was there no longer is in the database.

"Null" is just a placeholder for something that was previously there but is now no longer there, so instead of having a blank space where that server would have been, the word "null" will fill that space.

I believe it can also be a bug?

Don't quote me on that last sentence though.
